article.description: Jared Brownridge had 26 points on Saturday night and Santa Clara shot 61 percent in the second half to pull away for a 64-47 win over Pacific.
article.headline: Brownridge, Santa Clara use strong 2nd half to beat Pacific
article.linkText: Brownridge, Santa Clara use strong 2nd half to beat Pacific
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Jared Brownridge had 26 points on Saturday night and Santa Clara shot 61 percent in the second half to pull away for a 64-47 win over Pacific. Santa Clara opened the second half with 10 straight points and weathered Pacific's response -- a 9-2 run to get within 39-36 -- before steadily pulling away the rest of the way. Nate Kratch added 16 points and 10 rebounds and Emmanuel Ndumanya had seven points and 14 rebounds for the Broncos (14-13, 8-6 West Coast Conference). The Tigers (9-18, 3-11) trailed for most of the first half but Keshon Montague's half-court buzzer-beater tied it 27-all. Anthony Townes had 12 points and eight rebounds for the Tigers, who took 16 more attempts from the field than Santa Clara but made three less -- 19 of 61 compared to 22 of 45. The Broncos also outscored the Tigers 15-1 at the foul line.
